{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17505340","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17505340"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:29:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:29:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2430"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2430","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2430"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.01,0.01,0.2,0.63]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2430"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"57648"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2430","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2430"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2430"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43107"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"81"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1850"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1851"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1912"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17554"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"57648","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/57648"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 48-year-old man is being reviewed by his general practitioner. He has been diabetic for four years, his HbA1c is 10% and his BMI is 38 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E. He is hypertensive and is on metformin, simvastatin, and perindopril. He also has sleep apnoea. He has tried various diets and exercise programs with no sustained weight loss achieved. Furthermore, medical management has been unsuccessful despite multiple attempts over the past year. He would like to know about surgical options, particularly for the management of his diabetes and obesity.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following strategies is most appropriate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Laparoscopic gastric banding","Duodeno-jejunal exclusion tube","Vertical banded gastroplasty","Sleeve gastrectomy","Roux-en-Y gastric bypass"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe current indications for bariatric surgery include a BMI over 40 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E, or a BMI over 35 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E with one or more obesity-related comorbidities. Other indications include a BMI under 35 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E with type 2 diabetes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile all the surgical options have a place in the management of obesity, the \u003Cstrong\u003ERoux-en-Y gastric bypass\u003C/strong\u003E is typically preferred due to its high rate of weight loss and diabetic remission postoperatively. It is important that any bariatric surgery is supported by good quality perioperative care, including lifestyle modification and medical management.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELaparoscopic gastric banding\u003C/strong\u003E is less effective in terms of weight loss and diabetes remission compared to Roux-en-Y gastric bypass. It is also associated with complications such as band slippage and erosion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDuodeno-jejunal exclusion tube\u003C/strong\u003E is not a standard bariatric procedure and is primarily used in research settings. It is not widely accepted as a treatment for obesity or diabetes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVertical banded gastroplasty\u003C/strong\u003E has largely fallen out of favour due to inferior long-term weight loss outcomes and higher complication rates compared to other bariatric procedures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESleeve gastrectomy\u003C/strong\u003E is a viable option and can be effective for weight loss and diabetes control. However, Roux-en-Y gastric bypass is often preferred for patients with severe obesity and diabetes due to its superior outcomes in these areas.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOf note, medical management of obesity includes lifestyle changes such as diet and exercise, which are foundational but often insufficient alone for significant weight loss in patients with severe obesity. Pharmacotherapy can be considered, with medications like orlistat, liraglutide, or phentermine-topiramate, which may aid in weight loss. Addressing comorbidities such as hypertension and sleep apnoea is also crucial in the comprehensive management of obesity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Gastric bypass surgery can provide effective weight loss and diabetic control.","Roux-en-Y gastric bypass is preferred for significant weight loss and diabetes remission.","Bariatric surgery should be supported by lifestyle modification and medical management."],"references":["Ching Lee, P \u0026 Dixon, J 2017, \u0027Bariatric\u2013metabolic surgery: A guide for the primary care physician\u0027, Australian Family Physician, vol. 46, 7/01, pp. 465-471.","Wadden TA, Bailey TS, Billings LK, et al. Effect of Subcutaneous Semaglutide vs Placebo as an Adjunct to Intensive Behavioral Therapy on Body Weight in Adults With Overweight or Obesity The STEP 3 Randomized Clinical Trial. JAMA 2021; 10.1001."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43107"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2430"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMe